    },
    {
      "name": "Interview Sessions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Sessions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/processes/{{processId}}/sessions",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["processes", "{{processId}}", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "List sessions within a process.\n\nRole constraints:\n- **Candidate:** own process only — 403 if process doesn't belong to them\n- **Supporter:** own assigned sessions only\n- **Admin / marketer:** all sessions\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer, supporter, candidate\n\n**Response:** `200` — array of session objects (not paginated)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionId', pm.response.json().id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"supporterId\": \"{{userId}}\",\n  \"round\": \"1st round\",\n  \"mode\": \"Microsoft Teams\",\n  \"durationMinutes\": 60,\n  \"scheduledAt\": \"2024-02-15T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"description\": \"First technical screening\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/processes/{{processId}}/sessions",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["processes", "{{processId}}", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Schedule a new round within a process. `status` defaults to `SCHEDULED`.\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer\n\n**Response:** `201` — returns created session object. Test script stores `id` → `sessionId`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Session",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["sessions", "{{sessionId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Get session detail.\n\nRole constraints:\n- **Supporter:** own assigned sessions only\n- **Candidate:** sessions in their own process only\n- **Admin / marketer:** any session\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer, supporter, candidate"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Session",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"supporterId\": \"{{userId}}\",\n  \"round\": \"2nd round\",\n  \"mode\": \"Google Meet\",\n  \"durationMinutes\": 90,\n  \"scheduledAt\": \"2024-02-20T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"description\": \"Follow-up technical round\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["sessions", "{{sessionId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Update session logistics fields. All fields optional.\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer\n\n**Response:** `200` — returns updated session object."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Transition Session Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"IN_REVIEW\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["sessions", "{{sessionId}}", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Transition session status. Role constraints enforced server-side.\n\n`targetStatus` values: `IN_REVIEW | PASSED | REJECTED | NO_SHOW | CANCELLED`\n\nPermitted transitions by role:\n- **supporter:** `SCHEDULED → IN_REVIEW`, `IN_REVIEW → PASSED/REJECTED/NO_SHOW`\n- **marketer:** `SCHEDULED → CANCELLED`, `IN_REVIEW → PASSED/REJECTED/NO_SHOW/CANCELLED`\n- **admin:** any valid transition\n\nReturns `409` if the transition is not valid from the current status.\nReturns `403` if the caller's role is not permitted for the requested transition.\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer, supporter\n\n**Response:** `200` — returns updated session object."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Session Status History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/status-history",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["sessions", "{{sessionId}}", "status-history"]
            },
            "description": "Full audit trail of all status transitions for a session.\n\n**Roles:** admin, marketer"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
